The Online Examination System will be equipped with several core features designed to improve the examination process, ensure system security, and enhance the user experience. These features include:
1.	User Authentication:
o	Secure login system for students, teachers, and administrators, ensuring that only authorized users can access the platform.
o	Multi-role authentication to differentiate the capabilities and permissions of students, teachers, and administrators.
o	Integration with security protocols such as email verification, and, if needed, two-factor authentication (2FA) for additional security.

2.	Question Bank:
o	Teachers and administrators can create and store a wide range of exam questions in the system's question bank. This feature allows for the reuse of questions across multiple exams.
o	The system supports various types of questions, including multiple-choice, true/false, short answer, and essay-style questions.
o	The question bank will allow easy categorization and tagging of questions for future use, improving efficiency in exam creation.

3.	Online Exams:
o	Students will be able to take exams online from any location within a defined time window, allowing flexibility.
o	The system will display the exam questions, collect answers, and automatically grade objective questions like multiple choice and true/false.
o	Immediate feedback will be provided for objective questions, allowing students to view their results right after submitting the exam.

4.	Result Management:
o	Teachers and administrators will be able to view, store, and manage exam results, with automatic grading for objective questions.
o	Detailed reports on student performance will be generated, including analysis of results to help teachers identify areas of improvement for their students.
o	Exam results will be securely stored in the system, with provisions for backup and recovery to ensure data integrity.

5.	Admin Control:
o	Administrators will have comprehensive control over the platform, including the ability to add, remove, or manage users (students, teachers, and other administrators).
o	Admins will be able to oversee all aspects of exam creation, execution, and result management, ensuring the smooth operation of the system.
o	They will also have the ability to review system logs, monitor user activity, and manage permissions for different user roles.

